<paragraph blockId="4.[685,1172,1071,1730]" lastBlockId="5.[173,659,193,298]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="691" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">
This species is endemic to 
<collectingCountry box="[978,1050,1098,1119]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and has the widest distribution of all species of the genus. It is known from 
<collectingRegion box="[815,998,1151,1172]" country="Mexico" name="Distrito Federal" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Ciudad de México</collectingRegion>
and the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[685,771,1178,1199]" country="Mexico" name="Durango" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Durango</collectingRegion>
, Estado de 
<collectingCountry box="[877,952,1178,1199]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">México</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[960,1072,1178,1199]" country="Mexico" name="Guanajuato" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Guanajuato</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1080,1168,1178,1199]" country="Mexico" name="Guerrero" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Guerrero</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[685,764,1204,1225]" country="Mexico" name="Hidalgo" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Hidalgo</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[773,840,1204,1225]" country="Mexico" name="Jalisco" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Jalisco</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[848,929,1204,1225]" country="Mexico" name="Morelos" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Morelos</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[937,1010,1204,1225]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1019,1086,1204,1225]" country="Mexico" name="Puebla" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Puebla</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1095,1168,1204,1225]" country="Mexico" name="Sinaloa" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Sinaloa</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[685,755,1231,1252]" country="Mexico" name="Sonora" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Sonora</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[806,893,1231,1252]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="4" pageNumber="690">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
, occurring at elevations from 
<quantity box="[685,860,1257,1278]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" unit="m" value="3000.0" valueMax="4000.0" valueMin="2000.0">2,000 to 4,000 m</quantity>
. It is more commonly found in pine, oak, and pine-oak forests between 2,400 and 
<quantity box="[685,768,1310,1331]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" unit="m" value="2700.0">2,700 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Champion, G. C." box="[785,946,1310,1331]" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref3775" refString="Champion, G. C. 1884. Fam. Tenebrionidae (part) [pp. 1 - 88]. In: Biologia Centrali-Americana. Insecta. Coleoptera. Vol. IV, Part 1 (F. D. Godman and O. Salvin, editors). Porter, London, UK." type="book chapter" year="1884">Champion 1884</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Champion, G. C." box="[961,1012,1310,1331]" pageId="4" pageNumber="690" pagination="477 - 524" refId="ref3832" refString="Champion, G. C. 1892. Supplement to Heteromera [pp. 477 - 524]. In: Biologia Centrali-Americana. Insecta. Coleoptera. Vol. IV, Part 1 (F. D. Godman and O. Salvin, editors). Porter, London, UK." type="book chapter" year="1892">1892</bibRefCitation>
