<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="691" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="5.[173,659,347,700]" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">
<taxonomicName authority="(Champion, 1884) This" authorityName="This" baseAuthorityName="Champion" baseAuthorityYear="1884" class="Insecta" family="Zopheridae" genus="Verodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="691" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="interruptus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[221,611,347,368]" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[221,419,347,368]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">Verodes interruptus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Champion, G. C." box="[433,604,347,368]" pageId="5" pageNumber="691" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref3775" refString="Champion, G. C. 1884. Fam. Tenebrionidae (part) [pp. 1 - 88]. In: Biologia Centrali-Americana. Insecta. Coleoptera. Vol. IV, Part 1 (F. D. Godman and O. Salvin, editors). Porter, London, UK." type="book chapter" year="1884">Champion, 1884</bibRefCitation>
)
</emphasis>
This
</taxonomicName>
species and its synonym, 
<taxonomicName authority="Champion" authorityName="Champion" class="Insecta" family="Zopheridae" genus="Nosoderma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="691" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insigne">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">Nosoderma insigne</emphasis>
Champion
</taxonomicName>
, are cited from Las Vigas in 
<collectingRegion box="[173,257,429,450]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
and Capulalpam (Calpulalpan according to Selander and Vaurie (1962), but Capulalpam de Méndez is the correct name) in 
<collectingRegion box="[475,546,485,506]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Champion, G. C." pageId="5" pageNumber="691" pagination="1 - 88" refId="ref3775" refString="Champion, G. C. 1884. Fam. Tenebrionidae (part) [pp. 1 - 88]. In: Biologia Centrali-Americana. Insecta. Coleoptera. Vol. IV, Part 1 (F. D. Godman and O. Salvin, editors). Porter, London, UK." type="book chapter" year="1884">Champion 1884</bibRefCitation>
). The locality of Las Vigas needs confirmation due to a labeling mistake by the collector Höge, as many of his specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[455,539,568,589]" country="Mexico" name="Veracruz de Ignacio de la Llave" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">Veracruz</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[588,659,568,589]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
are mislabeled (
<bibRefCitation author="Delgado, L." box="[320,510,595,617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="691" pagination="319 - 332" refId="ref3985" refString="Delgado, L., E. F. Mora-Aguilar, and F. Escobar- Hernandez. 2012. Scarabaeoidea (Coleoptera) of the municipality of Xalapa, Veracruz, Mexico: Inventory and analysis. The Coleopterists Bulletin 66 (4): 319 - 332." type="journal article" year="2012">
Delgado 
<emphasis box="[407,454,595,617]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
). Foley and Ivie (2008), and 
<bibRefCitation author="Baselga, A. &amp; Recuero, G." box="[287,481,623,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="691" pagination="5060 - 5073" refId="ref3648" refString="Baselga, A., E. Recuero, G. Parra-Olea, and M. Garc'ia Par'is. 2011. Phylogenetic patterns in zopherine beetles are related to ecological niche width and dispersal limitation. Molecular Ecology 20: 5060 - 5073." type="journal article" year="2011">
Baselga 
<emphasis box="[367,414,623,645]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">et al.</emphasis>
(2011)
</bibRefCitation>
record this species from 
<collectingRegion box="[233,304,651,672]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="5" pageNumber="691">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
at elevations between 2,000 and 
<quantity box="[173,255,679,700]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="691" unit="m" value="3200.0">3,200 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
